Share this on WhatsAppA chopper has crashed into a building, killing two people so far in Lagos.
The aircrash happened around 12pm at Salvation Rd in the Opebi area of Lagos.
Two, of the three passengers on board, have been feared dead after the helicopter dropped into a building.
Early pictures of the incident revealed there was no emergency response going on. But subsequent ones showed first responders on the scene.
The aircraft belongs to Quorum Aviation.

				
